methods.get:
Gets the value at the given index.

:param index: (int) - index
:return: (IndexableDataWithDefault.T) value of this dataset at index
methods.getDefaultValue:
Gets the default value for this dataset.

:return: (IndexableDataWithDefault.T) default value for this dataset
methods.set:
Sets this datasets values equal to the values in another dataset.

:param data: (io.deephaven.plot.datasets.data.IndexableDataWithDefault<IndexableDataWithDefault.T>) - dataset to get values from.
methods.setDefault:
Defines the default value for this dataset.

:param v: (IndexableDataWithDefault.T) - value
methods.setSpecific:
Sets this datasets indexed values.

 If infinite is true, null values are returned for out-of-bounds indices. If not, an exception will be thrown.

Note: Java generics information - <TT extends IndexableDataWithDefault.T>

:param specificValues: (io.deephaven.plot.datasets.data.IndexableData<TT>) - data
:param infinite: (boolean) - if this dataset should return nulls for out-of-bounds indices.
methods.size:

:return: (int) the size of this dataset

text: IndexableData with a default value for missing indices and nulls.
